OK guys I'll be a bit lenient on the show for now, but I would say that if you watched shows such as The Event, Flash Forward, etc. you should expect about the same level of quality.

This show isn't "great", and it never will be on the level of a cable show, or anywhere near something like Lost was. The writing and the acting aren't there for that. The CGI is not very good either. 

This is another one of those shows that you watch as a fun cheesy sci-fi. Nothing more. Don't expect Breakign Bad here. It has annoying stereotypical teens on it. Stupid characters. Illogical science. The first episode is packed full of stuff and they don't really make much of a mystery of anything. 

That being said it has dinosaurs, time travel, and other weird shit.

So I've watched all possible episodes until the next episode (which is actually episode 5, check the OFFICIAL page of the show).

Far as reviews go, I'm going to watch for now, but I'm not very interested. I'm mostly just killing time between Dexter and The Walking Dead. As stated before, the acting is a little off, the plots are simple and unbelievably cliched.

This show has a Disney feel to me. Not that I'm hatin' on Disney, but it's clearly aiming for a slightly higher demographic than tweens.

Without giving any spoilers, for those who choose to invest in the show, everything happens way too fast, way too easily, and it gives me no sense of struggle, nor does it allow for any attachment to the characters. 5 hours in and I don't give a crap about any of them.

Also, the dinosaurs are not nearly terrifying enough. For 50 million, they should have hired better writers instead of set designers and computer nerds.

I've watched all the available episodes as of the current date, and I can safely say that it's well worth your time to watch.

7/10 acting
9/10 set/cgi
8/10 plot/story
8.5/10 overall.
